assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2017-05-16T19:02:25Z", "updated_at": "2023-03-20T18:49:03Z", "closed_at": "2023-03-20T18:49:03Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Playground link: https://is.gd/M1ruXP\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::borrow::Cow;\r\n\r\npub struct Foo<'a> {\r\n    foo: Cow<'a, str>,\r\n    bar: u8,\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn make_owned<'a>(borrowed_foo: Foo<'a>) -> Foo<'static> {\r\n    // error: cannot infer lifetime 'a (required 'a: 'static apparently)\r\n    // Foo{\r\n    //     foo: \"\".to_owned().into(),\r\n    //     ..borrowed_foo\r\n    // }\r\n\r\n    // but this of course works\r\n    Foo{\r\n        foo: \"\".to_owned().into(),\r\n        bar: borrowed_foo.bar,\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\npub fn main() {\r\n    let s = \"string\";\r\n    let borrowed_foo = Foo{foo: s.into(), bar: 42};\r\n    make_owned(borrowed_foo);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI've encountered this issue when trying to \"copy\" [this structure](https://docs.rs/gif/0.9.1/gif/struct.Frame.html) (`gif::Frame<'a>`) into a `'static` equivalent that replaces a borrowed buffer with an owned (empty) one, because I was only interested in the remaining fields.\r\nBut unfortunately, because unpacking such as above is incorrect, I had to meticulously [copy all the fields by hand](https://github.com/Xion/rofld/blob/2e3c01d953e855bcfd7b11c89f61aa0eaae75e26/src/util/animated_gif.rs#L64), even if I'm only using some of them.\r\n\r\nAs far as I understand, the limitation is that the unpacked & target type need to match exactly. This could perhaps be relaxed to follow the lifetime inheritance rules, in which case `'static: 'a` (specific `'a`) would imply that unpacking is, in fact, possible.", "closed_by": {"login": "Dylan-DPC", "id": 99973273, "node_id": "U_kgDOBfV4mQ", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/99973273?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Dylan-DPC", "html_url": "https://github.com/Dylan-DPC", "followe